<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>It would be great, if while creating a container will be possible to specify a title to a menu.
For instance let's take the code from docs:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code> 
/*
 * Create a container from an array
 *
 * Each element in the array will be passed to
 * Zend_Navigation_Page::factory() when constructing.
 */
$container = new Zend_Navigation(
'title'=&gt;'My Login Menu',
'content=&gt; array(
    array(
        'label' =&gt; 'Page 1',
        'id' =&gt; 'home-link'
    ),
    array(
        'label' =&gt; 'Zend',
        'uri' =&gt; '<a href="http://www.zend-project.com/">http://www.zend-project.com/</a>',
        'order' =&gt; 100
    ),
</code></pre>

<p>which will output  for example</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
</code></pre><h4><code>My Login Menu</code></h4><code>
</code><code>FirstPage&gt;
second Page
</code>

